ğŸ”· 1ï¸âƒ£ useReducer Hook

ğŸ§  What is useReducer?

`useReducer` is used for:

* Complex state logic
* Multiple related state values
* State transitions

ğŸ“Œ Alternative to `useState`
ğŸ“Œ Inspired by Redux

---

ğŸ§¾ Syntax

```jsx
const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, initialState);
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© Example: Counter using useReducer

```jsx
import { useReducer } from "react";

const initialState = { count: 0 };

function reducer(state, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    case "increment":
      return { count: state.count + 1 };
    case "decrement":
      return { count: state.count - 1 };
    default:
      return state;
  }
}

function Counter() {
  const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(reducer, initialState);

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{state.count}</h2>
      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: "increment" })}>
        +
      </button>
      <button onClick={() => dispatch({ type: "decrement" })}>
        -
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Cleaner for complex updates

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š useState vs useReducer

| useState         | useReducer       |
| ---------------- | ---------------- |
| Simple state     | Complex state    |
| Less boilerplate | Structured logic |
| Small components | Large logic      |

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 2ï¸âƒ£ useRef Hook (Deep Dive)

ğŸ§  What is useRef?

`useRef` is used to:

* Access DOM elements
* Store values without re-rendering

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Example: Focus Input

```jsx
import { useRef } from "react";

function InputFocus() {
  const inputRef = useRef();

  const handleClick = () => {
    inputRef.current.focus();
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <input ref={inputRef} />
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Focus</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Store Mutable Value (Without Re-render)

```jsx
const countRef = useRef(0);

countRef.current += 1;
```

ğŸ“Œ Updating ref does NOT re-render

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 3ï¸âƒ£ Component Composition Pattern

ğŸ§  What is Composition?

Instead of inheritance, React uses **composition**.

ğŸ“Œ Build complex UI using smaller components

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Example

```jsx
function Card({ children }) {
  return <div className="card">{children}</div>;
}

function App() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <h2>Title</h2>
      <p>Description</p>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ `children` allows flexible UI

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Passing Components as Props

```jsx
function Layout({ header, content }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <header>{header}</header>
      <main>{content}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 4ï¸âƒ£ Render Props Pattern

ğŸ§  What is Render Props?

A pattern where:

* A component receives a function as a prop
* That function returns JSX

ğŸ“Œ Used for logic sharing

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Example

```jsx
function MouseTracker({ render }) {
  const [position, setPosition] = useState({ x: 0, y: 0 });

  return (
    <div
      onMouseMove={(e) =>
        setPosition({ x: e.clientX, y: e.clientY })
      }
    >
      {render(position)}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Usage:

```jsx
<MouseTracker
  render={({ x, y }) => (
    <h2>
      X: {x}, Y: {y}
    </h2>
  )}
/>
```

ğŸ“Œ Flexible & reusable

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Composition vs Render Props

| Composition     | Render Props           |
| --------------- | ---------------------- |
| Uses children   | Uses function as prop  |
| Simple pattern  | More flexible          |
| Clean structure | Powerful logic sharing |

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ Common Mistakes

âŒ Overusing useReducer
âŒ Using ref instead of state
âŒ Overcomplicating render props
âŒ Not separating logic properly

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ” Use useReducer for complex logic
âœ” Use ref only when necessary
âœ” Prefer composition over inheritance
âœ” Use custom hooks instead of render props (modern way)
âœ” Keep components reusable

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Real-World Use Cases

* Complex forms (useReducer)
* Modal focus handling (useRef)
* Dashboard layouts (composition)
* Mouse tracking / reusable logic (render props)
* Drag & drop systems

